I"n<p>All participants must have their supervisor’s permission before they can work on an opportunity. Most participants are motivated individuals who are committed to the work.</p>

<p>Here are some tips to increase participation and commitment:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Clearly state the time commitment and the work expectations in the opportunity details.</li>
  <li>Follow up with participants to make sure they have the time to complete the work.</li>
  <li>Set realistic deadlines and schedule regular check-ins.</li>
  <li>Communicate often and make sure you’re available for and responsive to their questions.</li>
</ul>
